<FIRST>r a PM-Lites     09-18 0332</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lites,0344</SECOND>
<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHAMPLAIN, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The last of a band of fugitive monkeys are
leading captors on wild goose chases as they make themselves at home
in upstate New York.
   About 80 Japanese macaque monkeys swam from the Parc Safari game
preserve in Quebec to Clinton County in northeastern New York in
June. Most were quickly rounded up and returned to Canada, but the
remaining primates have been making monkeys out of their would-be
captors.
   One went window shopping in downtown Mooers recently and three
led searchers through a fast-food restaurant in the hamlet of
Champlain. One fell into a 45-gallon vat of french-fry grease. That
one didn't slip away, however.
   ``We know where they're at, and we've got a 95 percent chance of
getting them all back,'' said Dan Kyle, co-owner of the game park.
``There are three adults and two infants left.''
   The monkeys have been holed up along a highway between Mooers and
Champlain, sponging tidbits from passers-by, said Kyle, who promised
to round up the rest of the fugitives soon.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>TULSA, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Love comes and goes, but some love notes can
last a long time.
   Cindy Skinner, 16, was giving a customer change at a convenience
store when she spotted a dollar bill that served as a startling
reminder of a crush she and her best friend had on the same boy _
seven years ago.
   Miss Skinner and Dianna Braun, 16, decided to tell the world
about their crush on Timmy Anthamatten in 1982. They inscribed their
love for Timmy on separate dollar bills, but soon spent the money on
candy.
   The Summer of '82 came thundering back when Miss Skinner spotted
Miss Braun's love note in the cash register.
   ``I said, `Oh my gosh!' I told my supervisor about it and we
switched dollar bills,'' Miss Skinner said.
   Miss Braun has framed the dollar bill in her bedroom.
   ``Now I'm looking for Cindy's dollar,'' Miss Braun said.
</TEXT>
