<HEAD>Thunderstorms Rumble Over West</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms drenched Northern California today, and
scattered rain spread from the Florida Peninsula to coastal sections
of the Carolinas.
   Showers lingered from northwestern Wyoming to eastern Washington,
while storms struck northern Utah and southwestern Wyoming.
   In California, the remnants of Hurricane Octave struck heaviest
in the northern Sacramento Valley, where Redding received 2.21
inches of rain in 12 hours.
   On Sunday evening, thunderstorms in Montana produced 61 mph gusts
at Billings. High winds downed trees and power lines and damaged a
house and mobile home at Crow Agency.
   Heavier rainfall for the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT included
more than an inch at Red Bluff, Calif.
   Hurricane Hugo churned near Puerto Rico early today after
smashing through the French island of Guadeloupe and other Caribbean
islands. Forecasters said it was too early to tell whether Hugo
would strike the U.S. mainland.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
over Florida, the Carolina coasts, California, the northern Rockies
and North Dakota; and strong winds over the central Rockies and the
upper Mississippi Valley.
   Highs were expected to be in the 50s across northwest Montana; in
the 60s and 70s in the Pacific Coast, the central Rockies, the
northern Plains, the Great Lakes, the Ohio Valley, and the northern
and middle Atlantic Coast; in the 90s in the southern Florida
Peninsula, central and southern Texas, central Nebraska and the
desert Southwest; and in the 80s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 40
degrees at Burns, Ore., to 82 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. 57 foggy; Atlanta 66 fair; Boston 61 cloudy;
Buffalo 48 foggy; Charleston, S.C. 73 partly cloudy; Chattanooga 63
fair; Cincinnati 54 fair; Cleveland 54 fair; Detroit 51 foggy;
Hatteras 75 cloudy; Jacksonville 73 foggy; Key West 81 fair;
Knoxville 60 fair; Macon 61 fair; Miami 74 fair; New York 65 fair;
Philadelphia 61 fair; Pittsburgh 56 foggy; Portland, Maine 60
cloudy; Richmond 63 partly cloudy; Tampa 75 fair; Washington, D.C.
61 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 76 fair; Chicago 58 fair; Denver 66 fair; Des
Moines 62 fair; Fort Worth 66 fair; Indianapolis 54 fair; Kansas
City 63 fair; Little Rock 58 fair; Louisville 58 foggy; Memphis 61
foggy; Nashville 58 fair; New Orleans 72 fair; North Platte 64 fair;
Oklahoma City 62 fair; Omaha 67 fair; Rapid City 67 fair; St. Louis
63 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 62 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 48 foggy;
San Antonio 68 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 65 fair; Anchorage 44 rain; Boise 50 partly
cloudy; Casper 67 cloudy; Fairbanks 40 fair; Great Falls 43 rain;
Honolulu 78 fair; Las Vegas 68 windy; Los Angeles 63 partly cloudy;
Medford 51 cloudy; Pendleton 52 cloudy; Phoenix 79 fair; Portland,
Ore. 53 fair; Reno 49 partly cloudy; Salt Lake City 65 cloudy; San
Diego 64 fair; San Francisco 59 fair; Seattle 55 partly cloudy;
Spokane 50 rain.
   _International: Calgary 39 cloudy; Montreal 48 foggy; Ottawa 50
foggy; Regina 50 showery; Toronto 52 fair; Winnipeg 72 windy; Mexico
City 57 cloudy; Acapulco 75 rain.
