<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--TrainBlast     09-18 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Train Blast,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>Suicidal Farmer Caused Train Blast That Killed 24 in China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion that killed 24 people on a passenger
train near Shanghai was set by an impoverished farmer, the
government said Monday.
   The farmer, Zhou Wenzhi, was among those who died on June 26 when
dynamite exploded in a toilet at the front of a third-class
compartment of the train, the official Xinhua News Agency quoted the
Public Security Ministry as saying.
   Eleven people were seriously injured. The explosion on the
Hangzhou-Shanghai line occurred 20 miles southwest of Shanghai.
   Zhou, 25, from the suburbs of Yiwu in coastal Zhejiang province
acted because he was unable to repay $2,700 he borrowed for a
construction project, Xinhua quoted police investigators as saying.
</TEXT>
