<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Korea-Police     09-18 0099</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Korea-Police,0101</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thousands of Police Injured in South Korean Protests This Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nearly 7,000 policemen have been
injured so far this year in political and labor-related protests,
police said Monday.
   In a report to the National Assembly, the National Police
Headquarters said seven police officers were killed and 6,890
injured in dealing with 4,946 violent protests involving students
and workers so far this year.
   During the same period, police said 114 vehicles were destroyed
or burned, and 196 police stations and other government facilities
were attacked.
   Police gave no figures on civilian casualties.
