<FILEID>AP-NR-09-18-89 1641EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Nike     09-18 0224</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Nike,0234</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nike Posts 33 Percent Profit Gain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEAVERTON, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nike Inc. Monday reported a 33 percent
quarterly profit gain on an 18 percent increase in revenue.
   The athletic shoe and apparel maker said its net income grew to
$75.85 million, or $2.01 a share, in the first quarter of the
company's financial year, which ended Aug. 31. That was up from
$56.99 million, or $1.52 a share, a year earlier.
   Revenue for the first quarter came to $602.65 million, up from
$510.69 million a year earlier.
   Higher revenue was reported in all domestic footwear categories,
with the best gains from fitness and tennis, which grew 27 percent
and 48 percent, respectively. Revenue from domestic footwear
operations overall increased 16 percent.
   Domestic apparel revenue increased 22 percent while foreign
revenue was up 23 percent.
   Orders for footwear scheduled for domestic delivery from
September through next January are 37 percent above the prior year's
levels when measured in pairs of shoes. Future orders are up 52
percent when measured in dollars, the Beaverton-based company said.
   ``Our record results for the first quarter and strong futures
orders for the next five months reflect continuing strength across
all product categories,'' Nike Chairman Philip Knight said. ``Gross
margins benefited from this broad strength and from sound inventory
management. Nike's financial position continues to be strong.''
</TEXT>
