<SECOND>BC-AT&amp;T Calling,0102</SECOND>
<HEAD>AT&amp;T To Expand Long-Distance Plan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. said Monday
it will offer its Reach Out America long-distance calling plan in a
half-hour version for residential customers who don't make an hour
of calls a month.
   The Reach Out Half-Hour Plan, which is to go into effect Oct. 30
pending regulatory approval, will cost $4.35 a month for 30 minutes
of weekend and night out-of-state calling. Additional minutes of
weekend and night calling will cost 12 cents each.
   Customers also would receive a 10 percent discount on evening
calls.
